# Add 'make coverage' target (BISECT_ENABLE=yes dune runtest && bisect-ppx-report html)

## Requirements

- Add to `Makefile`:
  ```makefile
  coverage:
  	opam exec --switch=clawq-5.1 -- env BISECT_ENABLE=yes dune runtest
  	opam exec --switch=clawq-5.1 -- bisect-ppx-report html --output _coverage/
  	@echo "Coverage report: _coverage/index.html"
  ```
- Add `(preprocess (pps bisect_ppx))` to the `clawq_runtime` library stanza in `src/dune`. This enables instrumentation. Gate it with a dune condition or add it unconditionally (bisect_ppx no-ops when `BISECT_ENABLE` is not set).
- Add `_coverage/` to `.gitignore` if not already present.
- The `bisect_ppx` dep is already added via T002; this task wires the Makefile.

## Implementation Notes

`bisect_ppx` instruments the source at compile time. When `BISECT_ENABLE=yes` is set in the environment, it writes `.coverage` files during test execution. `bisect-ppx-report html` reads those files and generates an HTML report. The `_coverage/` directory should not be committed. Check if `src/dune` already has a `(preprocess ...)` stanza; if so, extend it rather than adding a new one. The unconditional approach is simpler — bisect_ppx overhead is negligible when not instrumenting.

## Acceptance Criteria

Done when:
- `make coverage` completes without error (requires `bisect_ppx` installed).
- `_coverage/index.html` is generated and shows non-zero line coverage for `src/memory.ml`.
- `make build` and `make test` are unaffected (bisect_ppx preprocess does not break normal builds).
- `make test` passes.
